body:
Hi Aymeric,

Let's see what may be causing the issue:

If this second time you got the same message as in the [photo you attached](http://www.grasshopper3d.com/group/ladybug/forum/attachment/download?id=2985220%3AUploadedFile%3A1612827), then your GDAL libraries are installed correctly. If they weren't you would have been informed about it.

So something is wrong with download of the raster data from the opentopography.org to your PC.
Let's try a couple of things:

1) Paste this link into your internet browser's address box (Firefox, Chrome ...) and hit Enter:

[http://opentopo.sdsc.edu/otr/getdem?demtype=SRTMGL3&west=-120.1...](http://opentopo.sdsc.edu/otr/getdem?demtype=SRTMGL3&west=-120.168457&south=36.738884&east=-118.465576&north=38.091337&outputFormat=GTiff)

Does that result in download of a file .tif?
If it does, then what is the size of that .tif file?
